description:
The appointee will report to the Director of Learning Support and will work within a multi-disciplinary Learning Support Team (LST). The appointee is expected to provide school-based counseling support for students on individual as well as group basis, work closely with parents and teachers, implement student well-being programs, collaborate with different teaching and pastoral teams whenever appropriate to ensure students’ diverse needs are met holistically.   

The ideal candidate will satisfy the following requirements:

Bachelor’s degree in Psychology/Counseling/Social Work or other relevant discipline; Master’s degree preferred;
At least 4 years of relevant counseling experience in working with children and adolescents;
Experience in implementing social and emotional learning or student well-being programs at school;
Experience in bilingual school setting preferred;
Proficiency in English and Mandarin (both written and verbal) with strong communication skills; and
Excellent interpersonal skills, case work and group work skills.

The ISF Foundation, Academy & Pre-School are committed to ensuring safety and well-being of our students. We hold high standards of recruitment practices with specific attention to child protection.  All applicants must be willing to undergo relevant background checks and screenings.  

Free Shuttle Bus travelling to and from The ISF Academy will be provided.

Application Deadline: 21 January 2022

Remuneration will commensurate with qualifications and experience. We will offer an attractive benefits package including medical, life insurance, and opportunities for professional development and continuing education to the right candidate. Please submit your application by completing the Application Form, Reference Check Statement which could be downloaded from our website: www.isf.edu.hk together with full Curriculum Vitae and Covering Letter. Please quote with our “Ref: no.” by email via "Apply Now".  

Personal data is collected for employment purposes only.

STUDENT AFFAIRS OFFICE
Associate Counsellor (Ref. 21122012-JCS)
Duties
The appointee will be required to:
(a)    provide counselling services to students individually and in groups;
(b)    handle cases in crisis situations under supervision;
(c)    design and conduct developmental programmes and university-wide events / campaigns for the promotion of psychological, physical and spiritual wellness of students;
(d)    work closely with academic faculties / departments in enhancing students’ holistic development;
(e)    conduct training for staff on campus and in student halls on issues concerning students’ psycho-social well-being and enhance their skills in handling students’ problems;
(f)    liaise with academic staff, family members and external agencies on matters relating to students’ well-being; and
(g)    perform any other duties as assigned by the Dean of Students or his/her delegates.
The appointee may be required to work irregular hours.
Qualifications
Applicants should have:
(a)    a recognised degree in Counselling, Psychology, Social Work or a relevant discipline;
(b)    at least five years’ relevant experience in counselling, preferably in educational setting and/or mental health setting;
(c)    the ability to demonstrate good skills in case management, interpersonal relationship and team work;
(d)    an excellent command of both written and spoken English and Chinese, with fluency in Putonghua being highly preferred; and
(e)    good servicing attitude.
Shortlisted candidates will be invited to sit for a written test.
Remuneration and Conditions of Service
A highly competitive remuneration package will be offered.  Appointment will be on a one-year gratuity-bearing contract.  Applicants should state their current and expected salary in the application.
Application
Please send a completed application form by post to Human Resources Office, 13/F, Li Ka Shing Tower, The Hong Kong Polytechnic University, Hung Hom, Kowloon, Hong Kong or via email by clicking "Apply Now".  Application forms can be downloaded from https://www.polyu.edu.hk/hro/careers/guidelines_and_forms/forms.  If a separate curriculum vitae is to be provided, please still complete the application form which will help speed up the recruitment process.  The closing date for application is Monday, 3 January 2022.  Applicants who are not invited to an interview within two months from the closing date should consider their applications unsuccessful.  The University’s Personal Information Collection Statement for recruitment can be found at https://www.polyu.edu.hk/hro/careers/guidelines_and_forms/pics_for_recruitment.
PolyU is an equal opportunity employer committed to diversity and inclusivity.  All qualified applicants will receive consideration for employment without regard to gender, ethnicity, nationality, family status or physical or mental disabilities.

STUDENT AFFAIRS OFFICE
Student Guidance Officer (two posts) (Ref. 21122013-JCS)
Duties
The appointees will be required to:
(a)    provide support in planning and organising programmes and activities for enhancing students’ all-round development;
(b)    assist in supporting students in their developmental agenda, e.g. providing guidance to students experiencing transient anxiety in the new learning environment;
(c)    coach and supervise student leaders / mentors / helpers to enable them to support and help fellow students in various developmental activities;
(d)    administer student surveys or evaluation of programmes / services including data collection, compilation of statistical reports and report writing;
(e)    supervise supporting staff on aspects related to programme implementation; and
(f)    perform any other duties as assigned by the Dean of Students or his/her delegates.
The appointees may be required to work irregular hours.
Qualifications
Applicants should have:
(a)    a recognised degree, preferably in Social Work, Psychology, Education or other relevant discipline;
(b)    some relevant experience, preferably in working with university students;
(c)    a good command of both written and spoken English and Chinese, with fluency in Putonghua being an advantage;
(d)    good computer literacy;
(e)    good servicing attitude; and
(f)    excellent interpersonal and communication skills.
Shortlisted candidates will be invited to sit for a written test.
Remuneration and Conditions of Service
A highly competitive remuneration package will be offered.  Appointment will be on a one-year gratuity-bearing contract.  Applicants should state their current and expected salary in the application.
Application
Please send a completed application form by post to Human Resources Office, 13/F, Li Ka Shing Tower, The Hong Kong Polytechnic University, Hung Hom, Kowloon, Hong Kong or via email by clicking "Apply Now".  Application forms can be downloaded from https://www.polyu.edu.hk/hro/careers/guidelines_and_forms/forms.  If a separate curriculum vitae is to be provided, please still complete the application form which will help speed up the recruitment process.  The closing date for application is Monday, 3 January 2022.  Applicants who are not invited to an interview within two months from the closing date should consider their applications unsuccessful.  The University’s Personal Information Collection Statement for recruitment can be found at https://www.polyu.edu.hk/hro/careers/guidelines_and_forms/pics_for_recruitment.
PolyU is an equal opportunity employer committed to diversity and inclusivity.  All qualified applicants will receive consideration for employment without regard to gender, ethnicity, nationality, family status or physical or mental disabilities.
